This paper discusses the evaluation of recommender systems, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also proposes a new evaluation protocol, which involves analyzing the performance of different algorithms, indicating a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the usefulness and trust of recommendations, which could be relevant to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
